{"word":"ἐσθλός","slug":"ἐσθλός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐσθλός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>much like <a href='S:ἀγαθός'><el>ἀγαθός</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>good</i> of his kind, <i>good, brave</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> in <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>;—also, <i>rich, wealthy</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>: <i>noble</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>κακός</el> (<a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:ἀγαθός'><el>ἀγαθός</el></a> 1), <el>εἴτ' εὐγενὴς πέφυκας εἴτ' ἐσθλῶν κακή</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>good, fortunate, lucky</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <el>ἐσθλά, τά</el>, <i>goods</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—but <el>ἐσθλόν</el>, <i>good luck</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>5. </b><el>ἐσθλόν [ἐστι]</el>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>it is good, expedient to</i> do, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}